<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="143" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[761,1350,285,712]" pageId="17" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName box="[764,867,285,318]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Caracal" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Caracal</taxonomicName>
were originally thought to be allied with 
<taxonomicName box="[895,1025,329,358]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Lynx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lynx">Lynx lynx</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1219,329,358]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Lynx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canadensis">L. canadensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Lynx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pardinus">L. pardinus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[889,993,372,397]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Lynx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufus">L. rufus</taxonomicName>
. However, recent genetic analyses show that the 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1187,403,436]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Felis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caracal">caracal</taxonomicName>
is not part of the 
<taxonomicName box="[875,932,442,475]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Lynx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lynx">lynx</taxonomicName>
group but rather is more closely allied with 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1212,481,514]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Profelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="17" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurata">Profelis aurata</taxonomicName>
. The two species are thought to have shared a common ancestor 4-85 million years ago. Nine subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
